gomodel:SYNGO_5376  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1c-f: confocal imaging of immunofluorescence labeling for ADF (Actin-depolymerizing factor, gene DSTN), Synaptophysin (SYP) and PSD-95 (DLG4) in cultured hippocampal neurons showed localization to both pre- and post-synapse.\n\nFigure 1g-i: immunogold EM of ADF in mouse CA1 and CA3 stratum radiatum showed localization to both pre- and post-synapse, with higher abundance in the former.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Preembedding electron microscopy Two mice were perfused with 2% paraformaldehyde ...\"\n\nantibody:\nrabbit anti-ADF (1:5,000; Sigma Aldrich)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
